<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59879">Profile!</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucamedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 5:05:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=395.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: EQ Legends servers.</span><hr size=1> I don't remember reading anything that precludes Verant from making a form of the game that costs more. They never said we are never going to make a premium service available, and actually foreshadowed this happening by having the &quot;Would you be willing to pay xxx dollars for a premium server&quot; survey months ago (maybe a year?).<br>
<br>
When you subscribed, you agreed to pay $10 a month for the service as is. Nothing is changing here except they are offering an even better service. The current one is not changing, and will not be changing. <br>
<br>
If you thought they were providing less than the agreed upon service, then you are free to cancel your account, and have been free to do that (if you didn't think you were getting good enough customer service or enough GM events) since you started playing. <br>
<br>
It would be bait and switch if they had said this was the premium service, and it is not going to get any better, but I don't remember reading that anywhere. They just had one plan, and you could either pay for that or not. Now they add a second one which offers better service, which will not effect those who do not sign up *at all*. <p><table style=filter:glow(Color="#0050FF")><td>Camedil Chaosweaver<BR>Phantasmist</td></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udshazzarinsoulstalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dshazzarin Soulstalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/3/02 7:41:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=395.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  EQ Legends Server</span><hr size=1> I'm not fond of this at all.  However, business is business, and since Sony has apparently conducted enough marketing research to support the numbers and potential profits, then I'm sure there is a profit waiting to be made.<br>
<br>
However, what angers me is that there are many bugs and features that haven't been worked out.  On one hand, no software company fixes *all* of its bugs before moving onward; however, features such as &quot;The Bizarre&quot;, et al, should definitely be top priority since Luclin was just released.  I think if anything, this Legends idea should have been postponed until some of the major things were worked out with Luclin.  <br>
<br>
Also, 40 bucks a month is too steep.  Several of the features they're offering you either don't need, or can get freely off the web.  Take Magelo, for example.<br>
<br>
I have done a significant amount of reading on many of the EQ fan sites, and no doubt, this has left a bad taste in many peoples' mouths.  Here we have Verant boasting about the features of this new server - many of which were promised in the original release of Everquest.  As a result, many are crying foul.<br>
